<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1928-02-25T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1928-02-25T17:00:00-05:00" n="254" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d254">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.113/1077: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Chargé in China</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Mayer</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-02-25T17:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">February 25,
                                        1928—5 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>67. Your telegram No. 119, February 23, 8 p.m.</p>
                        <list>
                            <label>1.</label>
                            <item>This Government is not involved in any express commitment by the
                                identic telegram quoted in paragraph 2 of Legation’s telegram and no
                                objection to its publication is interposed by the Department.</item>
                            <pb facs="0416" n="298" xml:id="pg_298"/>
                            <label>2.</label>
                            <item>The action taken by you as explained in paragraph 5 is noted by
                                the Department. Considering the facts detailed in Legation’s
                                telegram, the Department does not perceive any objection to the
                                proposal that the initiative be taken by the Japanese Government
                                with a view to inviting nonsignatory powers to participate in the
                                embargo.</item>
                        </list>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Kellogg</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>